Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for Next.js
================================================

Summary:
--------
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the FocusBill Next.js landing page.

Changes Made:
-------------

1. **Installed @vercel/speed-insights package**
   - Used npm (project's package manager) to install the latest version
   - Updated package.json and package-lock.json

2. **Modified src/app/layout.tsx**
   - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
   - Added <SpeedInsights /> component inside the <body> tag, after {children}
   - This is the correct placement for Next.js 14.2.3 with App Router

3. **Created .eslintrc.json**
   - Set up ESLint configuration with "next/core-web-vitals" preset
   - This was needed to run the linter for verification

Implementation Details:
----------------------
- Project uses Next.js 14.2.3 with App Router (confirmed by presence of app/layout.tsx)
- Used '@vercel/speed-insights/next' import path (appropriate for Next.js 13.5+)
- Placed component at the end of body tag to avoid blocking render
- Preserved all existing code structure and metadata

Verification:
-------------
✓ ESLint linting passed with no warnings or errors
✓ Project builds successfully (npm run build)
✓ TypeScript compilation successful
✓ No breaking changes introduced

Files Modified:
--------------
- package.json (added @vercel/speed-insights dependency)
- package-lock.json (updated with new dependency tree)
- src/app/layout.tsx (added SpeedInsights import and component)

Files Created:
-------------
- .eslintrc.json (ESLint configuration)

Notes:
------
The Speed Insights component will automatically track page loads and web vitals metrics
when the application is deployed to Vercel. No additional configuration is required.
The component is designed to have minimal performance impact and only sends analytics
data when running in production mode.
